# A safety margin, or savings.
#: ''Putting a little '''to weather'''''.  Creating a margin of safety, especially to [[err on the side of caution]]. In nautical use, a sailboat might aim windward of the target to avoid being [[set down]] to [[leeward]] by the wind or current, as well to be certain which direction to turn when approaching an unfamiliar shore.
